Key Match Events: James Harden had 24 points and 12 rebounds.
Ivica Zubac had 14 points and 12 rebounds.
Ochai Agbaji and Immanuel Quickley scored 21 points apiece for the Raptors.
Quickley hit a tying 3-pointer with 39 seconds left.
Powell and Harden combined to miss three of six free throws in the final moments.
Quickley and RJ Barrett missed tough short shots under defensive pressure before Jakob Poeltl missed a putback attempt with 4.1 seconds left.

Toronto was down three when Poeltl made his first free throw and intentionally missed his second, getting the ball to rebound right back to him. But he missed his 9-foot putback, and Harden threw the ball down the floor.
Post-Match Reflections: Kawhi Leonard still hasn't played this season while rehabilitating his right knee and won't travel on the Clippers' upcoming three-game trip, coach Tyronn Lue said.
Quickley was outstanding in the fourth quarter of his first appearance since missing eight games with a pelvic bruise.
LA showed resilience in its third set of back-to-back games already this season after winning in Sacramento on Friday.
Others: Kevin Porter Jr. had 15 points in his highest-scoring performance since returning to the NBA this fall after spending a year out of the league following a domestic violence assault charge in September 2023.
